# ACLs - Roteador Castanhal (R-CASTANHAL)

Regras aplicadas para garantir que:

- **VLAN 10 (Castanhal)** s√≥ se comunique com **VLAN 10 (Bel√©m)**
- **VLAN 20 (Castanhal)** s√≥ se comunique com **VLAN 20 (Bel√©m)**
- Bloquear comunica√ß√£o cruzada entre VLANs (local e remota)

---

## üîπ Redes envolvidas

### Castanhal
- VLAN 10: `192.168.110.0/24`
- VLAN 20: `192.168.120.0/24`

### Bel√©m
- VLAN 10: `192.168.10.0/24`
- VLAN 20: `192.168.20.0/24`

---

## üîπ Configura√ß√£o (aplicar no R-CASTANHAL)

> Aplica√ß√£o **INBOUND** nas subinterfaces:
- `Fa0/0.10` (VLAN 10)
- `Fa0/0.20` (VLAN 20)

```cisco
conf t

ip access-list extended CAST_VLAN10_POLICY
 permit ip 192.168.110.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.10.0 0.0.0.255
 deny   ip 192.168.110.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.20.0 0.0.0.255
 deny   ip 192.168.110.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.120.0 0.0.0.255
 permit ip 192.168.110.0 0.0.0.255 any

ip access-list extended CAST_VLAN20_POLICY
 permit ip 192.168.120.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.20.0 0.0.0.255
 deny   ip 192.168.120.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.10.0 0.0.0.255
 deny   ip 192.168.120.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.110.0 0.0.0.255
 permit ip 192.168.120.0 0.0.0.255 any

interface fa0/0.10
 ip access-group CAST_VLAN10_POLICY in

interface fa0/0.20
 ip access-group CAST_VLAN20_POLICY in

end
wr
